Class CReal

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.client.values.components.AbstractValue

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CloneableBlock, Checkable, ComponentElement, IdentHolder, ModelElement, SharedVariableSupport, java.awt.datatransfer.Transferable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable, javax.swing.undo.StateEditable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CDimless
    public abstract class CReal
extends AbstractCReal
implements IdentHolder, SharedVariableSupport
    This class provides a replacement for Real (CReal is shorthand for CAFEAN Real). Of particular noet: this element is a proper ComponentElement. This allows it to store a foreign-key reference to a user-defined real instead of encoding model and component idents within the value field.

    Any method which returns a CReal attempts to instantiate a new instance of the appropriate type; the calling object determines the returned type. For example, calling multiply on a Length a and a Width b with the call a.multiply(b) returns a new Length object (even though an extension called Area may exist, which would be more appropriate).

      • reconnectIdentReferences

        public void reconnectIdentReferences​(boolean preserveUnresolved,
                                     boolean useDbId)
        Description copied from interface: IdentHolder
        Resets this component's internal ident references to refer to appropriate components in the current AbstractModel. Intended for use after adding a component to a model and thus it's DB_ID will have been set to it's ident in the previous model. For ident references use find__ByDbId to find the new component, then store it's ident.

        Note: If this component's DB_ID is 0 this method does nothing.

        Specified by:
        reconnectIdentReferences in interface IdentHolder
        Parameters:
        preserveUnresolved - if true, ident references that aren't resolvable will be left dangling, if false, they will be set to 0.
        useDbId - if true, ident references will be reconnected via find_x_ByDB_ID; if false, ident references will be reconnected via find_x_ByIdent

      • equals

        public boolean equals​(java.lang.Object o)
        Two CReals are considered equal if one of the following is true:
        • they refer to the same SharedReal
        • neither has a valid reference, and both share a common value (two reals with NaN values are considered equal, even though NaN == NaN returns false).
        Overrides:
        equals in class AbstractCReal
        Parameters:
        o - the Object to be used for comparison.
        Returns:
        true if the blocks are equivalent, else false.
